pr_title: Implemented Pair Chat Management UI and Controller
pr_body:
This pull request introduces a significant enhancement to our application by implementing a comprehensive Pair Chat Management UI and Controller. This feature empowers users with an intuitive interface for managing and engaging in pair chats, fostering enhanced communication and collaboration. Partially resolves #114 

### Changes Made:

- Developed a modern and user-friendly Pair Chat Management User Interface (UI) that allows users to initiate, monitor, and actively participate in pair chats.
- Created a dedicated controller to manage the underlying logic and functionality of pair chat interactions, ensuring smooth communication and synchronization between users.
- Integrated the UI seamlessly with the existing application architecture, leveraging a modular design approach to minimize disruptions to the overall user experience.

pr_title: Migration: Firebase to Appwrite
pr_body:
This pull request migrates the existing functionality of Resonate from Firebase to Appwrite, a self-hosted backend server that offers similar features and functionalities (#63). This migration brings several advantages, including increased control over the backend infrastructure, improved scalability, and reduced reliance on third-party services.

### Changes Made

- Replaced Firebase authentication with Appwrite authentication services.
- Updated data storage and retrieval methods to utilize Appwrite's database instead of Firebase's Firestore.
- Made necessary modifications to ensure compatibility with Appwrite's SDKs and APIs.

### Benefits
- Enhanced Security: Appwrite provides robust security features, including server-side verification and authentication, protecting user data and ensuring secure communication.
- Scalability and Control: By migrating to Appwrite, we gain better control over our backend infrastructure, allowing us to scale resources according to project requirements.
- Reduced Dependency: Moving away from Firebase reduces our reliance on third-party services and gives us more flexibility in choosing backend providers.
- Cost Optimization: Appwrite offers flexible pricing options, potentially resulting in cost savings compared to Firebase.

### Checklist

- [x] The codebase has been refactored to use Appwrite APIs and SDKs.
- [x] Existing functionality has been thoroughly tested after migration.
- [x] Relevant stakeholders have been notified about the migration from Firebase to Appwrite.

Please review this pull request and provide feedback and suggestions for further improvements.

pr_title: Migration: Firebase to Appwrite
pr_body:
This pull request includes the migration of our project from Firebase backend to Appwrite backend. The migration process involved updating the necessary endpoints, and database interactions to align with Appwrite.

Key Changes Made:

- Replaced Firebase function calls with corresponding Appwrite function calls.
- Updated database queries and document structure to match Appwrite schema.
- Updated documentation to reflect the changes and provide guidance for future development.

pr_title: Appwrite Token Validation before serving API
pr_body: This pull request introduces a robust security enhancement to the project by implementing Appwrite token validation before serving API requests. With this update, we ensure that each API request is accompanied by a valid Appwrite token, enhancing the security and integrity of the data exchanged between the client and the server. It aligns with industry best practices for token-based authentication and authorization, making our application more robust and reliable. Necessary changes have been made in the Flutter App also. Closes #28

The previous PR for the same was closed since the branch had to be renamed for good documentation of the project history. Considering @jddeep review on my previous PR, work on points 1 and 2 above is done.

By attaching the JWT token to each request, we establish a secure and reliable channel for communication between the client and the server, ensuring that authorized users can access the API.

pr_title: Room Management Enhancements: Delete Room, Request Speaker Role, Admin Approval, and Kick out participant
pr_body:
This PR includes the following changes:
1. Admins can't leave the room rather they can delete the room.
2. If in any case, admin stops the app while in room, he can log back into the room as admin.
3. Listeners can raise/putdown hands to request speaker role in the room - Closes #89 
4. Admins can accept speaker requests and promote a listener to speaker
5. Admins can also demote a speaker to listener
6. Admins can kick out participants in their room


https://github.com/AOSSIE-Org/Resonate/assets/41890434/3ea99803-f97a-4004-ad63-7512b3baf6e7

pr_title: Enhanced Participant Sorting in Room Screen
pr_body:
This pull request introduces an essential enhancement to our application by implementing a robust participant sorting mechanism. The new feature allows seamless organization of participants within the room, enhancing user engagement and facilitating more effective communication during audio sessions. Closes #87 

Key Features of the Enhancement:

- Participant Sorting: We have added a dynamic participant sorting algorithm based on their role and activity within the room.
- Prioritized Order: Participants are now organized based on their roles as admins, moderators, speakers, and listeners, ensuring a clear hierarchy and smooth communication flow.
- Activity-Based Sorting: Within each role category, participants are further sorted based on their activity, such as raised hands or muted status, creating a more interactive and engaging environment.
- Real-time Updates: The sorting feature automatically adjusts as participants' roles and activity change during the audio session, providing an up-to-date view of the room dynamics.

Attached, you will find a demo video showcasing the sorting feature in action, providing a clear overview of how participants are dynamically organized within the app.

pr_title: Integrate Livekit for Audio Communication in Pair Audio Chat
pr_body:
This pull request represents a significant advancement in the Pair Audio Chat feature by seamlessly integrating Livekit WebRTC for high-quality audio communication. Building upon the existing functionality, this enhancement enables users to engage in real-time audio conversations, elevating the interactive experience. Closes #114 

### Changes Made

- Implemented the integration of Livekit WebRTC, a powerful Web Real-Time Communication technology, to enable audio communication within the Pair Audio Chat feature.
- Utilized Livekit's robust SDK to establish and manage real-time audio streams between users engaged in audio chats.
- Added feature to toggle microphone and loud speaker
- Ensured compatibility with various devices, providing a consistent audio communication experience.

pr_title: Implemented Pair Chat Management UI and Controller
pr_body:
This pull request introduces a significant enhancement to our application by implementing a comprehensive Pair Chat Management UI and Controller. This feature empowers users with an intuitive interface for managing and engaging in pair chats, fostering enhanced communication and collaboration. Partially resolves #114 

### Changes Made:

- Developed a modern and user-friendly Pair Chat Management User Interface (UI) that allows users to initiate, monitor, and actively participate in pair chats.
- Created a dedicated controller to manage the underlying logic and functionality of pair chat interactions, ensuring smooth communication and synchronization between users.
- Integrated the UI seamlessly with the existing application architecture, leveraging a modular design approach to minimize disruptions to the overall user experience.
